        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 8 at 4:05PM EDT by NWS Louisville KY</headline>
        <description>At 404 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Louisville, moving east at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Pea size hail and torrential rainfall.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Louisville, Jeffersonville, Jeffersontown, St. Matthews, Lyndon,
Middletown, Douglass Hills, Prospect, Hurstbourne, and
Graymoor-Devondale.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
